<!--Toggle tool bar: converts desktop to mobile screen bar
rightclick-inspect-console-screenwidth,screen height

screen resolutions for all devices
extra smalll:    <576px                          -old phones
small screen:    >576px and <768px               -mobile_phones
medium screen:   >768px and <992px               -tablets
large screen:    >992px and <(1200px and 1366px) -desktop,laptops
extra large:     >(1200px and 1366px)            -big monitors

1900px : extra extra large

html:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"/> name,attributes are content
viewport says what type of view/display either mobile,lappy
content says to know what type of device is,
width defined the device-width and initial-scale defined in what view it starts either top,bottom,left,right
without this we can't build responsive

css:
max-width-small
min-width-large

@media(screen value is going to be given in here){
    
}
-->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
        <title>bs</title>
        <style>
            body{
                background-color:peru;
            }
            /*for tablet*/
            @media(max-width:992px) and (min-width:894px){
                body{
                    background-color:purple;
                }
            }
            
        </style>

    </head>
    <body>

    </body>
</html>
